1
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,500
"Love After Addiction"

2
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:26,600
(Episode 5)

3
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,879
Yoki, where are you going?

4
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,879
To make you trust me.

5
00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:34,879
Alright, alright.

6
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,319
Alright, I trust you, OK?

7
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,879
You trust me now?

8
00:01:44,159 --> 00:01:45,280
Then take a sip.

9
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,840
Does it taste good?

10
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:55,599
It's good.

11
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,080
Now tell me about yourself.

12
00:01:59,159 --> 00:02:01,359
A college student from the city,

13
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,000
why would you want to be a volunteer

14
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,240
in this small fishing village?

15
00:02:08,599 --> 00:02:09,759
Me?

16
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:12,759
At first,

17
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:14,119
I just wanted to escape my dad

18
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,520
and find a place to catch my breath.

19
00:02:17,159 --> 00:02:18,479
Then I came here—Lanwan Village.

20
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,439
Every wisp of sea breeze here

21
00:02:21,039 --> 00:02:22,599
and every tide...

22
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:25,760
I think this place is really worth
being discovered by more people.

23
00:02:27,499 --> 00:02:28,560
You joining the show

24
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:30,319
is for the same reason too?

25
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,280
Yang Meng.

26
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,240
Count me in!

27
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,319
I'll join you.

28
00:03:11,199 --> 00:03:12,240
Want to get on the boat?

29
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Get on the bed?

30
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,680
Here?

31
00:03:19,039 --> 00:03:20,039
Isn't...

32
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,199
Isn't it right here?

33
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,800
He just grilled fish for me.

34
00:03:30,039 --> 00:03:31,159
And now he's making me work.

35
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,639
What kind of person is he?

36
00:03:32,759 --> 00:03:34,519
He changes faces
faster than turning a page.

37
00:03:34,879 --> 00:03:36,159
I'm not your coolie!

38
00:03:37,879 --> 00:03:38,879
No way.

39
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,840
I need to relax.

40
00:03:56,193 --> 00:03:58,345
(Miscelaneous gay
flirting leading to a hookup)

41
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,360
So close!

42
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,519
No way...!

43
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:36,519
Surprised?

44
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:26,519
What happened to them now?

45
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,000
The liking is real.

46
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:59,279
And the physical attraction

47
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,120
is real too.

48
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,720
What should I do?

49
00:07:52,376 --> 00:07:53,816
(A string of voice notes from "Dad")

50
00:07:55,199 --> 00:07:56,920
Li Mei from your village
sent me a message.

51
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,480
She said there's some
problematic celebrity...
Brother Meng

52
00:07:59,121 --> 00:08:00,319
I want breakfast.

53
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,720
You promised to come back this month.

54
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,160
Are you going to break your promise?

55
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,120
What exactly is in that village?

56
00:08:17,759 --> 00:08:19,079
I already found a job for you.

57
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,735
If you don't come back within a month,

58
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:21,839
I'll come there to get you.

59
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,600
You're a man.

60
00:08:24,601 --> 00:08:26,279
So we should communicate like men.

61
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Dad,

62
00:08:30,279 --> 00:08:31,519
I have my own dreams.

63
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,080
I want to...

64
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,840
Study hard and get into a good university!

65
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:36,280
Then find a good job
that matches your major!

66
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,360
Dad.

67
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,280
After graduating from
university, I want to...

68
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Brother Meng.

69
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,159
What's for breakfast?

70
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,720
Make it yourself.

71
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,360
I'm busy.

72
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,440
What's wrong with you now?

73
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,360
You won't even make me food!

74
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:13,639
I'm starving, I'm starving.

75
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:18,000
Starving me to death, starving me to death.

76
00:09:35,587 --> 00:09:36,786
What's this?

77
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,159
Why is this here?

78
00:09:40,184 --> 00:09:42,024
[Unhinged fan text
wishing Yoxi happy birthday]

79
00:09:47,235 --> 00:09:49,685
[That fan account from earlier
that was wishing him luck]

80
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:19,399
Five minutes and twenty-four seconds.

81
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:21,639
And this one...

82
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,440
is our professional islander.

83
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,000
Since he was a kid,

84
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,679
he's been messing around in these waters.

85
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,519
He has very solid

86
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:31,960
water skills.

87
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:33,679
What about our guests?

88
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,159
Is there anyone

89
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,520
who wants to compete with him?

90
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,720
The winner

91
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:39,480
will get extra monetary support.

92
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,920
The more people you defeat,

93
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:43,080
the more survival funds

94
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,240
you'll get.

95
00:11:44,919 --> 00:11:46,639
Which guest wants to take the challenge?

96
00:11:56,639 --> 00:11:57,679
If no one does,

97
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:02,039
then I'll do it!

98
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,600
So masculine!

99
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,759
No wonder he's famous—it's inevitable!

100
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:18,440
I'm afraid something bad
might happen to him.

101
00:12:19,465 --> 00:12:21,541
[Amount of time elapsed]

102
00:12:35,044 --> 00:12:37,904
["I can't hold it any
longer, but I can't give up!"]

103
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,519
It won't be that bad.

104
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,360
Brother Yoki,

105
00:12:47,159 --> 00:12:48,359
Don't let anything bad happen!

106
00:12:49,919 --> 00:12:51,199
Are you trying to kill yourself?

107
00:12:58,399 --> 00:12:59,399
Yoki

108
00:12:59,799 --> 00:13:00,799
Yoki, wake up!

109
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:02,039
Yoki.

110
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:41,759
H-He...
H-He...

111
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,080
He's awake!

112
00:13:45,159 --> 00:13:46,199
I really don't understand.

113
00:13:46,919 --> 00:13:48,279
This big fool!

114
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,240
Actually, last night...

115
00:14:01,279 --> 00:14:03,080
Let's go, Brother Yang, let's take a bath!

116
00:14:03,559 --> 00:14:04,159
Let's go!

117
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,360
Yang Meng!

118
00:14:06,759 --> 00:14:07,759
What's up?

119
00:14:08,559 --> 00:14:09,360
It's none of your business.

120
00:14:09,559 --> 00:14:10,559
Get lost!

121
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:11,840
Yang Meng

122
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,480
Yoki.

123
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,799
Mind your own business!

124
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,679
If you dare harass Yang Meng again,

125
00:14:17,879 --> 00:14:19,880
I won't mind
adding another scandal to your name,

126
00:14:20,639 --> 00:14:21,840
making you fall even harder!

127
00:14:23,399 --> 00:14:23,840
Let's go.
I have training later.

128
00:14:24,679 --> 00:14:25,679
Go in first.

129
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,120
Stop right there!

130
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,720
You're so dark!

131
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,480
Let's go!

132
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:45,759
Brother Yoki!

133
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,600
Taking a bath?
Wanna go together?

134
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,360
Are you crazy?

135
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,600
Uncle Chen,

136
00:15:27,039 --> 00:15:28,039
have you seen Yang Meng?

137
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,159
Little Meng,

138
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,360
he got roped into playing
the Fairy of Flowers.

139
00:15:31,679 --> 00:15:32,279
Dress up as a flower fairy?

140
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,440
Yes.

141
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,120
Well，well.

142
00:15:59,679 --> 00:16:01,200
Look, the flower fairy is coming out.

143
00:16:03,519 --> 00:16:04,679
So beautiful.

144
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,639
Actually, quite nice—very pretty!

145
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,320
He's shy! He's shy!

146
00:16:17,759 --> 00:16:18,919
So beautiful!

147
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:20,840
Thank you for voting for me today.

148
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:22,519
But dressed like this...

149
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:24,440
isn't it a bit inappropriate?

150
00:16:24,639 --> 00:16:25,679
I like you so much!

151
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:26,919
Very beautiful! Very beautiful!
So pretty! So pretty!

152
00:16:28,279 --> 00:16:29,279
Brother Yang!

153
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,759
I have to take some photos

154
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:31,879
to show to my Uncle Yang

155
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:32,960
his beautiful daughter!

156
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:33,799
Yes, yes.

157
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,840
Just kill me today!

158
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,079
If my dad finds out I'm dressed like this,

159
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,840
he'll beat me to death!

160
00:16:37,039 --> 00:16:37,879
Just teasing you!

161
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,159
I'll keep them for myself.

162
00:16:40,679 --> 00:16:41,799
Isn't it really nice?

163
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,719
Yes, yes! It's nice!

164
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:44,758
Is our village's Flower Fairy beautiful?

165
00:16:44,759 --> 00:16:45,799
Beautiful!

166
00:16:45,919 --> 00:16:47,200
Turn around for everyone to see!

167
00:16:47,919 --> 00:16:48,999
Just turn around.

168
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:49,600
Turn around.

169
00:16:49,601 --> 00:16:51,121
Turn around, turn around, turn around.

170
00:17:34,319 --> 00:17:35,960
The bonfire party has started.

171
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,640
Alright, alright, alright.

172
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,319
Let's go, let's go dancing.

173
00:17:39,839 --> 00:17:41,599
Let's go, let's go.

174
00:17:41,839 --> 00:17:43,039
Let's dance!

175
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,160
Why are you dressed like this?

176
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,440
Say something!

177
00:18:00,119 --> 00:18:01,479
That old man couldn't fit into it.

178
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,039
He begged me to come help.

179
00:18:04,119 --> 00:18:04,680
One hundred!
No!

180
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,160
Two hundred!
Still no!

181
00:18:07,039 --> 00:18:07,599
Five hundred!
Still no!

182
00:18:08,559 --> 00:18:09,559
Ten thousand!

183
00:18:10,079 --> 00:18:11,079
I'm not buying it.

184
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:13,040
You're the little flower boy!

185
00:18:17,119 --> 00:18:18,119
But I remember...

186
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:18,839
that old man's figure

187
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,120
isn't even as good as yours!

188
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,160
You mean...

189
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,359
my figure is good?

190
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,640
Narcissist!

191
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:32,319
Then do you think...

192
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,880
I'm handsome?

193
00:18:35,519 --> 00:18:36,519
No.

194
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,720
Tell the truth!

195
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,680
Do I look good?

196
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,440
No.

197
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,960
But I think...

198
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,160
you look really nice today!
